$ gcc -x

Force the compiler to compile in the specified language, regardless of the suffix of the source code.

In the following example, `foo.cpp` is treated as a c file rather than a c++ file, although its suffix is `.cpp`:
code {
$ gcc -x c foo.cpp
code }

